methods.name: <init>
methods.comment:
Construct a new instance of this class that uses the default name and group and specifies the min
 and max values for the range.

params.name: minValue
params.comment: the min value of the acceptable range.

params.name: maxValue
params.comment: the max value of the acceptable range.

params.name: editorProvider
params.comment: an object that can provide an appropriate range editor for the column type.

methods.name: <init>
methods.comment:
Construct a new instance of this class that specifies the name and group and specifies the min
 and max values for the range.

params.name: name
params.comment: the constraint to use instead of the default "Not In Range".

params.name: minValue
params.comment: the min value of the acceptable range.

params.name: maxValue
params.comment: the max value of the acceptable range.

params.name: editorProvider
params.comment: an object that can provide an appropriate range editor for the column type.

params.name: group
params.comment: the group to use instead of the default value of "number".

name: NotInRangeColumnConstraint
comment:
Column Constraint where acceptable column values are outside some range defined by a min value and
 a max value.
